<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2790> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2790" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent by the Senate to assist Anicius in making a settlement in Illyria (Liv. 45.17.4, and 26.11-15)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2609> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2609" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 42.9.8; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 50f., 123, 458f.; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod. The first plebeian college of Consuls (Fast. Cap.). Both Consuls were assigned to Liguria (Liv. 42.10.10-12). Popillius supported the unjust acts of his brother (Cos. 173) against the Statelliates despite senatorial criticism and decrees (Liv. 42.10.10-12, 21.1-5, 22.1 and 5) and returned late to report on Liguria and hold{411} the elections (42.28.1-3). Aelius instituted the debate on the acts of Popillius but was overawed by his colleague (42.10.9-11). See below, Praetors, on Crassus; and on Popillius, see Lübker, no. 3." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2543> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2543" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Under the Lex Villia Annalis his praetorship must fall in this or a previous year, and the earlier places are filled." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2542> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2542" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the Praetors of 175, see especially Münzer, APF 218f." .
